James Azania, Lokoja  The National Inland Waterways Authority (NIWA) on Tuesday said that it has released water buses and patrol boats for use by relevant states and federal agencies in the fight against the Coronavirus pandemic. The Dr George Moghalu- led NIWA had last week donated N10 million to the National Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) and the Lagos State government in fight against the deadly Coronavirus disease. Moghalu had directed that all infrastructures, including ferry terminals, dockyards, river ports, jetties, watercrafts, barges and tug boats nationwide be sanitized and the highest level of hygiene maintained. NIWA in a statement in Lokoja, Kogi State, on Tuesday, a copy of which was made available to The Nation, announced that: “Further to our earlier financial contributions, the Managing Director, National Inland Waterways Authourity, Chief Dr George Moghalu has authorized the release of the authority’s water-buses, security patrol boats and other craft for use by relevant states’ and federal agencies in the fight against the COVID-19 pandemic. “These crafts are useful for moving personnel and materials to and from the riverine communities, as well as maintaining security on our inland waterways.” He urged users of the waterways to observe safety precautions, social distancing and other guidelines, as given by the Presidential Taskforce on COVID-19, “in order to stay safe in these trying times.”